		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						) Sublimanda bona omnia: aut
						circumvenient Mala.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>All good things must be raised: or bad things encircle them.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian" marginalia_continues_from="Ha2.189v_0001" marginalia_from_transcription="Ha2.189v.xml" book_id="FolgersHa2" id="Ha2.190r_0001">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						<!-- Continued from facing page, tail, Ha2.189v --> [p. 202: Qui in summis nauigat, in nummis anchorat. =]
						= Magnoru[m] negociatoru[m] axioma chrematisticum.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>[p. 202: He who navigates in the highest spheres, anchors in money.] The money-making axiom of the greatest business.</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						Corpus ante omnia debet respondere Animo: et quo&agrave;d fieri potest, etiam status
						Oeconomicus. Qualis est animus, tale esse debet illius instrumentum.
						Militaris animi Corpus debet esse solidum, robustum, velox; laboris
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="270">
					<marginalia_text>
						patientiss[im]u[m] ad omnia dexterrimum.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
			Before all, the body ought to respond to the mind; and as far as one can, even one's economic condition.
			The instrument of the body must be such as the mind.
			The body of the military mind ought to be solid, robust, and quick; and most skillfully capable for all types of work.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian" marginalia_continues_to="Ha2.189v_0002" marginalia_to_transcription="Ha2.189v.xml" book_id="FolgersHa2" id="Ha2.190r_0002">
